        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 8:38PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 836 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorms
between Buckingham and Charlotte Court House, moving northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.  Very Heavy Rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible. Flooding of
poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Buckingham...
Appomattox...
Keysville...
Charlotte Court House...
Dillwyn...
Phenix...
and Redoak.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
